    pingouin.list_dataset¶

    pingouin.list_dataset()¶

    List available example datasets.

    Returns
    datasetspandas.DataFrame

    A dataframe with the name, description and reference of all the datasets included in Pingouin.

    Examples

    >>> import pingouin as pg
>>> all_datasets = pg.list_dataset()
>>> all_datasets.index.tolist()
['ancova',
 'anova',
 'anova2',
 'anova2_unbalanced',
 'anova3',
 'anova3_unbalanced',
 'blandaltman',
 'chi2_independence',
 'chi2_mcnemar',
 'circular',
 'cochran',
 'cronbach_alpha',
 'cronbach_wide_missing',
 'icc',
 'mediation',
 'mixed_anova',
 'mixed_anova_unbalanced',
 'multivariate',
 'pairwise_corr',
 'pairwise_tests',
 'pairwise_tests_missing',
 'partial_corr',
 'penguins',
 'rm_anova',
 'rm_anova_wide',
 'rm_anova2',
 'rm_corr',
 'rm_missing',
 'tips']
